The '''Association for Law, Property and Society''' is a scholarly organization for researching engaging in the study of property law and social issues. The association hosts an annual conference,<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=EobDCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA170 |page=170 |title=Protest, Property and the Commons: Performances of Law and Resistance |author=Lucy Finchett-Maddock |publisher=Routledge |date=2016}}</ref> the first of which occurred at [[Georgetown Law]] in 2010,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allard.ubc.ca/events/conference-association-law-property-society |title=Conference: Association of Law, Property & Society|publisher=Peter A. Allard Hall}}</ref> and is also the publisher of the journal ''Law, Property and Society''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://road.issn.org/issn/2373-5856-journal-of-law-property-and-society-#.Wd-7cltSzIU |title=JOURNAL OF LAW, PROPERTY AND SOCIETY |publisher=Road Open Access}}</ref> The current president of the association is Douglas Harris of the [[Peter A. Allard School of Law]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://alps.syr.edu/about-us/association-for-law-property-and-society-officers-and-board-of-directors/ |publisher=ALPS |title=Officers and Board of Directors}}</ref>
