{{Politics of Seychelles}}
<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Palais de Justice, Seychelles.jpeg|The Seychelles' courts building known as '''''Palais de Justice'''''|thumb|250px|right]] -->
The '''Constitutional Court of Seychelles''' is a specialized and independent court in [[Seychelles]]. The court's primary role is to protect the [[civil right]]s of the people of Seychelles. It is precided by any three judges of the [[Supreme Court of Seychelles|Supreme Court]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sites.google.com/site/theseychelleslegalenvironment/judiciary/the-constitutional-court|title=The Constitutional Court|website=The Seychelles Legal Environment|date=|accessdate=7 September 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.seychellesnewsagency.com/articles/5279/Seychelles'+court+rejects+presidential+election+petitions%2C+validates+President+Michels+win|title=Seychelles' court rejects presidential election petitions, validates President Michel’s win|work=[[Seychelles News Agency]]|location=Victoria Seychelles|author=Sharon Uraine|date=31 May 2016|accessdate=7 September 2016}}</ref>

